NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|If you play 2 way Checkback, over 1NT a bid of both 2@C and 2@D by responder are artificial. 2@C shows an invitational hand. 2@D shows a game forcing hand (and is often used to explore for slam, even perhaps in a minor suit). There are a lot of subtleties, but the basic 2 way Checkback, even if you want to skip the subtleties is pretty easy to play.|
PG| ***** 29 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|If responder bids 2@C it is up to opener to get to game if he has a maximum hand.|
PG| ***** 30 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|If responder bids 2@D, then the auction is easy because a game force has been established. You have lots of room to explore for the best contract, including slam. The advantage of 2 way Checkback is the 2@D game forcing bid.|
